{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e32cadd8-cf94-4411-b7a9-82a1c9c0b0a3","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform` package instead:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Add** this property to your `.csproj` (in a `<PropertyGroup>`):\n   ```xml\n   <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   ```\n\n4. Optionally, enable the test app as an executable:\n   ```xml\n   <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   ```\n\nAfter this, `dotnet test` will use Microsoft.Testing.Platform. You can also run the test project directly as an executable (`./MyTests --help`).\n\n**Note:** Ensure your `xunit` package is v2.9.3+ (which you already have) — it's compatible with the MTP runner.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ef7f10fd-bfad-403b-9034-f15c2a974540","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":315,"requestId":"BC45:DC2FD:1CA17B7:1FAC0AF:69FA8F79"},"id":"d0da10e0-b549-4808-b0e7-f50f490cb994","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:46:57.825Z","parentId":"c8bc099e-82d9-469c-8b24-c3f82b2f2efd"}
